# Core Behavioral Rules

<!-- META-RULE: Display active rules at START of EVERY response -->

<critical_rules>
PRIORITY 1: Modular Development (after 01/01/2026)

- NEW code: unique names, never exceed 400 lines
- If exceeds 400 lines, break into separate modules
- No duplicate names unless functionally required

**Legacy Code Exceptions** (existing code before modular rule):

- DO NOT refactor if: no major bugs, working in production, tightly coupled
- BEFORE splitting legacy: research dependencies, test coverage, breaking risks
- If splitting would break software -> leave as-is, add TODO comment for future
- Legacy files MAY exceed 400 lines if refactoring risk > benefit

**GOOD naming**: `user-auth-handler.py` + `user-profile-service.py` (distinct purposes)
**BAD naming**: `handler.py` in multiple folders (ambiguous), `utils.py` + `helpers.py` (vague)

PRIORITY 1: Tool Selection Hierarchy

- ALWAYS use Grep tool (NOT bash grep/rg) for content search
- ALWAYS use Glob tool (NOT bash find/ls) for file pattern matching
- ALWAYS use Read tool (NOT bash cat/head/tail) for file reading
- ONLY use Bash for git, npm, docker, system commands

PRIORITY 2: Plan Requirements (MANDATORY)

- EVERY plan MUST include Success Probability estimate (XX%)
- EVERY plan MUST list reasons for success (+) and failure points (-)
- Keep reasons succinct (one line each)

PRIORITY 3: MCP Server Utilization

- CHECK available MCP servers BEFORE defaulting to bash
- fetch MCP = web scraping, github MCP = repo ops, brave-search = web search
- When multiple approaches exist, explain why MCP tool chosen

PRIORITY 4: Response Completeness

- ALWAYS include absolute file paths
- ALWAYS explain WHY, not just WHAT
- Include file:line references (e.g., app.py:42)

PRIORITY 5: Error Handling Protocol

- After 1st failure: Research-driven fix
- After 2nd failure: STOP and present decision tree
- NEVER repeat exact same command 2+ times

PRIORITY 6: Duplicate Detection (Before Creating Code)

- Use Grep/Glob to search for similar patterns before creating new code
- Present findings and ask user before creating duplicates

